<br>
A couple of people told me 12 was too low for the zone but I really didn't have any problems with yard trash. I didn't die once in the four levels. There is a great XP bonus here which means between half and a full blue of XP per dark blue mob killed.<br>
<br>
Loot is OK (the mushrooms the beetles drop sell to merchatns for a few gold), but not great. Keep any Zombie skins you get as occasionally higher level types come looking for them for Pottery. I got some nice buffs and a bit of cash in return for half a stack.<br>
<br>
I had two camps. The first at the tunnel entrance clearing up the 3 or 4 spawns in the front yard. This is great if the zone is quiet. But if it's busy it means you have to zone every 5 minutes because of trains. Which is a huge pain (/mourn pet)<br>
<br>
Camp 2 was on a little raised bit of land just next to the gazebo. I didn't seem to agro anything sitting there and trains were a lot rarer. The downside here is that it was tougher to single pull. Although with an earth pet at full health and me with 50 mana or more I could usually handle 2 blue cons at once.<br>
<br>
If I pulled more than 2 it was time to gate or run like hell. <br>
<br>
Tactics? the usual I assume. Buff pet, park pet, pull to pet, nuke and/or tank where appropriate. Fun at 12 and 13 but started getting a bit boring afterwards.  <br>
